reality television clich&eacute;, she's definitely here to make friends.</p>\n<p>Eden discovered her love of writing at a particularly inconvenient time, when she had just finished her undergraduate degree in Psychology.</p>\n<p>Knowing that she cared more about her deadlines for the student paper than she did about her p-values and statistical methods (sorry mum and dad), she decided to earn some hands-on experience in the media industry, as well as complete an Honours year in English Literature.</p>\n<p>She finished her thesis on Cyborg Feminism a year later, analysing the ways in which science fiction and the philosophy of roboticism has influenced the women's liberation movement.</p>\n<p>She is unsure how she ever thought this would lend her any degree of employability, but she loved every second of writing it.</p>\n<p>Before joining the Channel 9 family, Eden was a freelance journalist, writing for The Sydney Morning Herald, ABC News and Crikey, and a production assistant for Channel 7's The Morning Show and The Daily Edition.</p>\n<p>She also spent three weeks in Nevada covering Bernie Sanders' 2016 presidential bid from within his campaign offices, and has published news and analysis articles in both English and French for bilingual publications Le Courrier Australien and Le Petit Journal.</p>\n<p>Eden began working at Nine as a video producer for 9News, moving assam with Adam Liaw.</p>\n<p>She then went on to work behind the scenes as a producer on Nine&rsquo;s major reality shows such as Married At First Sight, The Block and Love Island. She is also a writer, producer and occasional host for FBi Radio's news and politics show, Backchat, on Saturday mornings.
